==Russian==
===Etymology===
From [[–Љ—С–і]] ([[honey]], [[mead]]) and [[-–µ–і]] ([[eater]]), hence literally "''one who eats honey''". There is also a folk etymology from [[–Љ—С–і]] and [[–≤–µ–і–∞—В—М]] (to [[know]], to [[manage]]), hence "''one who knows honey''" or "''a master of honey''".

